Here's the plan:                                                                

 1 app/api/items/route.ts — A real backend with GET, POST, and DELETE handlers. 
   It checks for SUPABASE_URL + SUPABASE_ANON_KEY; if present, it talks directly
   to Supabase's REST API via fetch (no extra SDK dependency needed, so it won't
   break your build if the package isn't installed). Otherwise it falls back to 
   an in-memory array — zero config, works immediately. Data model: a tutoring  
   listing (tutor name, subject, hourly rate, available slot, description).     
 2 app/page.tsx — A polished, single-page marketplace: a "Post a listing" form  
   on the left, and a live grid of "Open slots" on the right. Booking a slot    
   removes it (calls DELETE), which is the real create/list/delete flow.        
   Includes loading skeletons, an inviting empty state, and an error state with 
   retry.                                                                       

