Note on Supabase: if you set SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, the route      
expects a Postgres table named listings with columns id (uuid, default          
gen_random_uuid()), tutor_name (text), subject (text), hourly_rate (numeric),   
available_slot (text), description (text), and created_at (timestamptz, default 
now()), with RLS policies allowing the anon key to select/insert/delete. Without
those env vars, it just works out of the box with the in-memory store.          

