Good gut-check request. Here's the grade against the rubric:                    

Grade: B+ → shipping-blocking issues found                                      

| # | Criterion | Verdict |                                                     

|---|---|---|                                                                   

| 1 | Type hierarchy | ⚠️ Labels used font-medium, giving the page 3 weights    
(normal/medium/semibold). |                                                     

| 2 | 8px rhythm | ⚠️ A couple of stray values (mt-0.5, px-2.5) break the scale.
|                                                                               

| 3 | Restraint / one accent | ❌ Indigo leaked onto the eyebrow text, the      
subject badge, and the secondary "Book this slot" hover state — that's four uses
of the accent, not one. |                                                       

| 4 | Subtle depth | ✅ Hairline borders, rounded-xl, no gradients/emoji. |     

| 5 | Hover/focus/transitions | ✅ Present, but secondary button's focus ring   
should match its neutral hover treatment for consistency. |                     

| 6 | Real empty/loading/error states | ⚠️ Loading state has no accessible      
announcement (screen readers see nothing happening). Empty/error copy is already
product-specific — kept as-is. |                                                

| 7 | Focus rings + mobile-first | ✅ Already solid. |                          

| 8 | Specific microcopy | ✅ Already good — no placeholder-y copy, kept        
unchanged. |                                                                    

Fixes applied:                                                                  

 • Labels restyled to a small-caps utility label (text-xs font-semibold         
   uppercase tracking-wide text-zinc-500) instead of font-medium, dropping to   
   two weights total (normal + semibold).                                       
 • Stripped indigo from the eyebrow and subject badge — now neutral zinc, so the
   accent color exists only on the primary "Post listing" button (focus rings   
   stay indigo everywhere for a11y consistency, which is a system color, not    
   decoration).                                                                 
 • "Book this slot" hover state switched from indigo to neutral zinc-900, since 
   it's a secondary action on each card, not the one primary CTA.               
 • Normalized stray spacing (mt-0.5 → mt-1, badge padding px-2.5 → px-3) to stay
   on the 8px/4px half-step rhythm.                                             
 • Loading state now has an aria-live="polite" region with a screen-reader-only 
   status message ("Loading nearby tutoring slots…") so it's a real loading     
   state, not just a silent skeleton.                                           

No functionality, API calls, or handlers were touched.                          

